main event: On October 10, 1966, three unidentified objects were observed in Waterloo, Iowa for a duration of 4 hours.
interesting points: The objects moved in a north-west direction,Two smaller objects moved in a straight line while the larger one moved erratically,One observer reported that the large white object changed color to flickering red before stopping,The observation took place on a clear night, indicating good visibility,The report lacked sufficient data for a definitive conclusion.
sighted object: three unidentified objects in the sky
witness description: Two housewives in Waterloo, Iowa, ages 27 and 32; reliability unknown.
